The paper discusses general systems theory and its application to computer science, specifically highlighting the debt that contemporary research still has with Leibniz's system. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Cybernetics (cs.CY), or Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
